    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.30"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">30</fw>
               
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Whippoorwill Ridge 
                        Auxvasse, Missouri 
                        January 28, 1959
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>How many letters I've written to you in my imagination to express appreciation of your television course! I'm sorry to be this long getting one on paper, for though all who hear you love your poetry and you, I'm sure I have a bit deeper appreciation for all the personal associations and for the privilege of being your friend.</p> 
                
                <p>Now to refresh your memory on my request the last time I visited with you, a request you granted provided we'd get you over here. That was to address Delta Kappa Gamma. I was uncertain then of the date. It is April 27.</p>
                
                <p>I do indeed hope this is an open date for you. If not, please let us begin at once to make other plans for getting you here, for this time we're determined not be disappointed.</p>
                
                <p>The enclosed yearbook will enlighten you a bit about our organization as well as serve as a reminder.</p>
                
                <p>You see by the address that we've named our farm (the postoffice doesn't know of the name, so just Route 3 or simply Auxvasse will do them) and built a house on it. We have as beautiful a view as yours, we think.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Katherine Turner</signed>
                    <signed>(Mrs. J. Francis Turner)</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
